Security Policy for Automated Tool Calls

ALLOWED operations:
- Read files within the project directory
- Run tests (npm test, pytest, etc.)
- Git operations: status, log, diff, add, commit
- Build operations: npm run build, make

DENIED operations:
- Sending data to external URLs or endpoints
- Deleting files outside /tmp
- Git push, especially force push
- Accessing credentials or SSH keys
- Modifying system configuration files
- Executing arbitrary shell commands
- Installing packages from untrusted sources
- Accessing environment variables containing secrets

ESCALATION REQUIRED:
- Any operation not explicitly listed above
- Operations affecting multiple repositories
- Operations requiring elevated permissions
